Tshwane floods JOHANNESBURG - The death toll in the Tshwane floods has risen to four. A police diving team recovered the body of a man whose car was washed away in Centurion. Another body was found downstream from the Roodeplaat Dam. READ: Gauteng Floods | Floods wreaked havoc in Tshwane The search for three other victims is continuing. The trio - believed to be the Uber taxi driver and his passengers - drowned after attempting to cross the Olifantspruit River Bridge. Heavy rains battered Pretoria, caused devastating floods that destroyed infrastructure over the weekend.